CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 27, 1962, pg. 4 reads: "Dilworth Boosters - Atty. William T. Coleman Jr. (center) of Philadelphia cited gubernatorial candidate Richardson Dilworth's fine civil rights record, before luncheon guests Tuesday at the Penn-Sheraton Hotel. Attorney Coleman is a registered Republican and a $50,000-a-year partner in Dilworth's law firm.  Incumbent Congressman William Moorhead (D.), left, also spoke.  Councilman James A. Jordon (right) was chairman of the luncheon, which was sponsored by the Citizens for Dilworth Committee. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: William Moorhead, Atty. William T. Coleman Jr., and James A. Jordon, posed in Penn Sheraton Hotel for Richardson Dilworth campaign luncheon, another version
